@startuml path_ready_to_lidar_target_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Path Ready To Lidar Target State Signal Flow\n(path readiness + object safety -> LDR health/target publish)

participant "Object safety /\npath-ready inputs" as SafetyCtx #F4F7FB
participant "LDR\nlidar state owner" as LDR #E8F7E8
participant "Lidar state bus" as LidarBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / ADAS consumers" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Lidar Inputs ==

SafetyCtx -> LDR : objectConfidence\nobjectEventCode\nobjectTrackValid\nobjectFailSafeMode\npathReady
LDR -> LDR : if objectSafetyInputStale then\nconfidence = 0 / track = 0 / failSafe = 0
LDR -> LDR : targetDetected = clamp(objectTrackValid, 0, 1)
LDR -> LDR : if pathReady == 0 or failSafe >= 2\nthen health = 0 and targetDetected = 0
LDR -> LDR : freeSpaceClass from targetDetected + confidence
note right of LDR
Representative gating inputs
- pathReady
- objectTrackValid
- objectConfidence
- objectFailSafeMode
end note

== Lidar Publish ==

LDR -> LidarBus : frmLidarStateMsg\nLidarHealth / TargetDetected / FreeSpaceClass
LDR -> LidarBus : Confidence / RangeBucket
note right of LDR
Representative outputs
- LidarHealth
- TargetDetected
- FreeSpaceClass
- Confidence
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

LidarBus -> Obs : lidar target-state readback /\nADAS sensor consumers

note over SafetyCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Object safety and path readiness reach LDR
2. LDR decides whether target tracking is trustworthy
3. LDR publishes health, target-detected, and freespace state
4. ADAS and observers consume the effective lidar target posture
end note

@enduml
